urn-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616863\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xaf1665702630029.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xaf1665702630029.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xaf1665702630029.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xaf1665702630029\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Dimmed Background Color (DimmedBackColor)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determines whether the background color of the widget is changed when the field syntax is <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIM</code>, so the field cannot get focus or be edited.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__p_d102995e1_d102996e1_d102997e1\">DimmedBackColor\n                                <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">False</code>\n</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12134e1_d12135e1_d12136e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12134e1_d12135e1_d12136e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12134e1_d12135e1_d12136e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12134e1_d12135e1_d12136e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">True</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12134e1_d12135e1_d12136e1__entry__2\">\n The background color is changed when the field is dimmed.\n <p class=\"p\">For the Combo Box and Drop-Down List widget, this is the system default dimmed color, which is normally grey. For other widgets, it is changed to the color of the parent entity or form.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12134e1_d12135e1_d12136e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12134e1_d12135e1_d12136e1__entry__2\">\n The background color of the field is not changed when the field is dimmed.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__section_vcg_4ph_wwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d362466e124\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__table_d12137e1_d12138e1_d12139e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Dynamic?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Supported in Grid?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Dependencies:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Field Syntax = <code class=\"ph codeph\">DIM</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__section_jfk_qph_wwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d362466e191\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__p_d103004e1_d103005e1_d103006e1\">When a field is dimmed, which means that the field\n            syntax is set to DIM, the text displayed (that is, the foreground color) is set to grey.\n            The DimmedBackColor enables you to change the background color as well.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__note_r45_rph_wwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> The default <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> file sets\n            this property <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>, thereby overriding the default value for this\n            property. To apply the default value, remove this property from the default widget\n            definitions in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__section_irk_tph_wwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d362466e212\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__ul_nvq_5ph_wwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__li_d41540e1_d41541e1_d41542e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zfr1695290811319.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zfr1695290811319.html\" title=\"Start the Microsoft Windows Color dialog box.\">colorbox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__li_d41543e1_d41544e1_d41545e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vmo1688449724415.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmo1688449724415.html\" title=\"The ucombobox widget combines an input field with a drop-down list. It allows users to select one item from a previously defined list, or enter their own data instead. It is applicable only to form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called ComboBox, which is mapped to ucombobox.\">ucombobox (Combo Box)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__li_d41546e1_d41547e1_d41548e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fud1688450548955.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fud1688450548955.html\" title=\"The udropdownlist widget is a field-level widget that can display a list of valid options in a list below the input field, so that the user can select one. It is applicable only to form components.\">udropdownlist (DropDownList)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__li_d41549e1_d41550e1_d41551e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"klb1688454363706.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/klb1688454363706.html\" title=\"Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\">EditBox</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__li_d41552e1_d41553e1_d41554e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rez1688451198680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rez1688451198680.html\" title=\"The ulistbox widget is a field-level widget that displays an open list in which one or more values can be selected. It can only be used in form components.\">ulistbox (ListBox )</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xaf1665702630029__li_d41555e1_d41556e1_d41557e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lxs1665702651483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lxs1665702651483.html\" title=\"The uspinbutton widget enables the user to enter or select a numeric value by clicking a button to increase or decrease a value by a predefined interval within a predefined range. Uniface provides a logical widget called SpinButton, which is mapped to uspinbutton.\">uspinbutton (SpinButton)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616863\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616863\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Dimmed Background Color (DimmedBackColor) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Dimmed Background Color (DimmedBackColor) Determines whether the background color of the widget is changed when the field syntax is DIM , so the field cannot get focus or be edited. DimmedBackColor = True | False Value Description True The background color is changed when the field is dimmed. For the Combo Box and Drop-Down List widget, this is the system default dimmed color, which is normally grey. For other widgets, it is changed to the color of the parent entity or form. False The background color of the field is not changed when the field is dimmed. Usage Dynamic? Yes Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: Field Syntax = DIM Description When a field is dimmed, which means that the field syntax is set to DIM, the text displayed (that is, the foreground color) is set to grey. The DimmedBackColor enables you to change the background color as well. Tip: The default usys.ini file sets this property off , thereby overriding the default value for this property. To apply the default value, remove this property from the default widget definitions in the .ini file. Applies To colorbox ucombobox (Combo Box) udropdownlist (DropDownList) EditBox ulistbox (ListBox ) uspinbutton (SpinButton) Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}